TITLE.0: 3nd Beta version NOAA/SEL GOES_6 CDF Energetic Particle Flux

TEXT.0: The NOAA GOES satellites include 2 sensors: an Energetic Particle Sensor (EPS), and a Magnetometer (MAG).

TEXT.1: The satellites are geostationary. For older satellites, inclination may be up to 15 deg.

TEXT.2: Data sometimes contains errors. especially GOES-6 EPS & possibly both  GOES 6,7 magnetometers.

TEXT.3: The EPS data are 5-min. averages, the MAG data are 1-min. averages.

TEXT.4: The NOAA Space Environment Lab (SEL), Space Environ. Services Center (SESC) uses this data in real time for forecasting and monitoring.

TEXT.5: Reference: GOES Spacecraft OperationsManual, Volume I, May 1980, Hughes RefNo. D5150 SCG 00169R

TEXT.6: GOES-8, with 3 electron sensors should launch in early 93: the IE variables will be defined post-launch.

TEXT.7: For additional info., contact Dave Bouwer, NOAA/SEL, Mail Code R/E/SE, 325 Broadway, Boulder, CO 80303 USA (303)497-3899.

MODS.1: Corrected S/C location error & added Geographic (not geodetic) & GEO S/C positions.  -db, 16 Feb 93

MODS.2: Added unit_ptr to s/c position units fixed CATDES on SC_pos_sm, fixed GSn   -db, 20 Apr 93
